## Overview

Complete the File System Access API (FSA) auto-save feature by building comprehensive UI and user onboarding. The auto-save code already exists in `src/services/autoSave.ts` but has no user-facing interface. This task will create a Settings UI, first-time onboarding modal, platform-specific documentation, and testing to make FSA auto-save production-ready.

**User Problem:**
Users need a way to backup their data across devices without relying on Neuman Brain servers (100% client-side architecture). They need guidance on setting up auto-save to a cloud folder (iCloud, Google Drive, OneDrive, Proton Drive, Dropbox) that syncs automatically.

**Technical Problem:**
Auto-save infrastructure exists but no UI to:
1. Enable/configure auto-save
2. Guide users to pick a cloud-syncing folder
3. Show backup status and manage preferences
4. Provide platform-specific instructions (Windows/macOS)

