## Design Considerations

### Design System Compliance
- **Colors:**
  - Primary: `accent-blue` for folder picker button
  - Success: `status-success` for "Backup enabled" status
  - Warning: `status-warning` for reminder badges
  - Text: `text-light-primary`, `text-dark-primary`
  - Surfaces: `surface-light`, `surface-dark`, `surface-light-elevated`, `surface-dark-elevated`
- **Components:**
  - Modal component for onboarding
  - Bento card pattern for Settings sections
  - Gradient buttons for primary actions
- **Typography:**
  - Headings: `text-lg font-semibold` (modal headings)
  - Body: `text-sm` (instructions)
  - Labels: `text-xs text-secondary` (helper text)
- **Spacing:**
  - Section gap: `gap-6`
  - Form gap: `gap-4`
  - Button padding: `px-4 py-2.5`
- **Animations:** None (simple modal transitions via Modal component)
- **Dark Mode:** All colors use semantic tokens for auto dark mode support

### Performance
- **Bundle Size Impact:**
  - BackupOnboardingModal: ~15KB (lazy load via React.lazy)
  - BackupSettings: ~10KB (lazy load with Settings page)
  - Total impact: +25KB (acceptable, stays under 100KB main bundle)
- **Lazy Loading:**
  - BackupOnboardingModal should be lazy loaded (only loads when triggered)
  - BackupSettings lazy loads with Settings page (already implemented)
- **Optimization:**
  - Platform detection happens once (cached)
  - Cloud provider instructions rendered conditionally

### Accessibility
- **Keyboard Nav:**
  - Tab through modal steps
  - Enter to advance/confirm
  - Escape to close modal
  - Arrow keys for cloud provider selection
- **Screen Reader:**
  - Modal title: `aria-label="Backup Setup"`
  - Step indicators: `aria-label="Step 1 of 5"`
  - Folder picker button: `aria-label="Choose backup folder"`
  - Configuration options: Clear labels for all inputs
- **Focus Management:**
  - Focus trapped in modal when open
  - Focus returns to trigger element on close
  - First interactive element receives focus on open

